snippet.title: Mickey Mousecapade (NES) - Gameplay | No Commentary
snippet.description:
Mickey Mousecapade, released in Japan as Mickey Mouse: Fushigi no Kuni no Daibouken, is a platform game developed by Hudson Soft and published by Capcom originally in 1987 for the Family Computer (Famicom) in Japan. Capcom released the game for the Nintendo Entertainment System (NES) in the United States.

▌NES Gameplays Playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLXEHhSievieFgfGxSd8m552ndmpzvj5mJ
